         <abstract>
            <p>A finite-difference method for the solution of symmetric positive linear differential equations is developed. The method is applicable to any region with piecewise smooth boundaries. Methods for solution of the finite-difference equations are discussed. The finite-difference solutions are shown to converge at essentially the rate 0(h&lt;sup&gt;1/2&lt;/sup&gt;) as h → 0, h being the maximum distance between adjacent mesh-points. An alternate finite-difference method is given with the advantage that the finite-difference equations can be solved iteratively. However, there are strong limitations on the mesh arrangements which can be used with this method.</p>
          </abstract>
